  <h1>Learn more about the cognitive-based tactics used by Day-by-Day</h1>
  <div class="container">
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Gratefulness:</strong> Also known as gratitude, Gratitude is a powerful tactic that can significantly improve someone's mental well-being. It involves cultivating a genuine and appreciative attitude towards the positive aspects of life, no matter how small. By actively practicing gratitude, individuals can experience a wide range of psychological and emotional benefits that contribute to their overall mental health and well-being.</li>
      <li><strong>Reframing:</strong> A cognitive tactic used to shift one's perspective and find positive or constructive meaning in a difficult or challenging situation. It involves looking at a situation from a different angle or interpreting it in a way that highlights the potential benefits or learning opportunities, rather than focusing solely on the negative aspects. Reframing can help individuals cope with adversity, foster resilience, and turn setbacks into opportunities for personal growth and development.</li>
      <li><strong>Compassion:</strong> A tactic and emotional response that plays a crucial role in alleviating suffering, both for ourselves and others. It involves recognizing the pain, struggles, or distress of others and responding with empathy, care, and a genuine desire to help. Compassion can bring comfort, support, and understanding to those in need, fostering a sense of connection and kindness that can ease suffering in various ways.</li>
      <li><strong>Visualization:</strong> A cognitive technique that involves creating mental images or representations to achieve a specific goal. It leverages the mind's ability to simulate experiences and scenarios in a way that can positively impact motivation, problem-solving, performance, and overall success in various endeavors. Whether used in sports, business, personal development, or any other field, visualization can be a potent tool for achieving desired outcomes.</li>
      <li><strong>Feel Emotions:</strong> A natural and essential part of being human. Emotions provide valuable information about our inner experiences, help us process events, and guide our actions. Feeling our emotions can help us feel more grounded and better prepared to make decisions. It can also help us clear our mind and feel more rested.</li>
      <li><strong>Foregiveness:</strong> A profound act of love and compassion that can play a significant role in alleviating suffering, both for oneself and others. It involves letting go of resentment, anger, and the desire for revenge, and instead, choosing to respond with understanding, empathy, and acceptance. By embracing forgiveness as an expression of love, individuals can experience healing, find inner peace, and create an environment of harmony and understanding.</li>
    </ul>
